==English==
=== Etymology===
From Greek '''hērōs'''

=== Noun ===
'''hero''' (''plural'' '''[[heroes]]''')

#A real or mythical person of great bravery who carries out extraordinary deeds.
#A [[role model]].
#The main male [[protagonist]] in a work of fiction.
#A [[champion]].
#A large sandwich made from meats and cheeses.

